            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>

            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>

            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>

            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>

            </td>
            <td>
            <div class='map-sidebar'>
            
            <h3>Map Legend</h3>
        
            <div class="map-legend">
                <h4>Subspecies</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/b-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Anthus-trivialis?query=ssp:%22haringtoni%22'>haringtoni</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>Witherby, 1917</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/a-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Anthus-trivialis?query=ssp:%22trivialis%22'>trivialis</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></span></li></ul><h4>Unclassified</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/unspec-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">No subspecies specified</span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/bg-12.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">In background of another recording</span></li> </ul>
            </div>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

        </td>
        
        <td>2014-04-23</td>
        <td> 07:10</td>
      
        <td>Netherlands</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=52.127&long=4.323&loc=Meijendelse+Berg%2C+Meijendel%2C+Wassenaar%2C+ZH">Meijendelse Berg, Meijendel, Wassenaar, ZH</a>
        </td>
        <td>10</td>
        <td>song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>South facing slope with thorn scrub and scattered Scotch Pine, bordering Oak wood and overlooking a large valley system with arteficial lakes. Several other Tree Pipits can be heard singing and calling in the background. Bird sings from and between tops of Oak and Pine. Dissapears regularly out of sight. In the last minute he is down to the suspected nesting site and starts singing again from a low branche. Minimum recording distance c 10m. [52.126994,4.324468, ul140503]</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Aberrant song - similar to that of Blue-headed Wagtail (Motacilla (flava) flava), a species that breeds at the same location. Habitat more open than usual in Tree Pipit. Behaviour and optical appearance of the bird quite normal with typical song in flight.</p>

        <td>flight call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>One individual in migratory flight. The traditionnal "piiiz", but also a strange "impure" call, two times. Generally in flight migratory anthus trivialis can alternate "piiiz"  and the "si" uttered during breeding season near the nest. Here, the "impure" calls seem to be a failed "si"... </p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>

            <ul class='genus'>

            </li>

        <td>France</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=48.3671&long=2.6213&loc=For%C3%AAt+de+Fontainebleau+%28near++Fontainebleau%29%2C+Seine-et-Marne%2C+%C3%8Ele-de-France">ForÃªt de Fontainebleau (near  Fontainebleau), Seine-et-Marne, Ãle-de-France</a>
        </td>
        <td>140</td>
        <td>nuptial calls ( ?) </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>This is a rare call I have just recorded two or three times in 9 years . Always uttered from the ground, it's constitued by a serie of ascending and then descending notes. And beteween those notes, the bird utters the traditionnal "si" territorial call. Always uttered at the begining of the breeding season, perhaps during the nest construction, it could be a kind of copulating incitement. See also <a href='/146356'>XC146356</a>.</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>

        <td>France</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=48.5597&long=1.9914&loc=Longvilliers%2C+Yvelines%2C+%C3%8Ele-de-France">Longvilliers, Yvelines, Ãle-de-France</a>
        </td>
        <td>160</td>
        <td>nuptial calls ( ?) </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>This is a rare call I have just recorded two or three times in 9 years . Always uttered from the ground, it's constitued by a serie of ascending and then descending notes. And beteween those notes, the bird utters the traditionnal "si" territorial call. Always uttered at the begining of the breeding season, perhaps during the nest construction, it could be a kind of copulating incitement. See also <a href='/146359'>XC146359</a>.</p>

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Two birds, but only on is not far from me. Migratory halt. First perched, and then flying off. Two kinds of calls: first traditionnal "piiiz" flight calls. But also at <a onclick='xc.playFrom(146350, 24);'>00:24</a>, two "si" calls, generally uttered near nest, but also in migratory flight. They are so different than the "piiiz" calls than, in migratory flight, it's always difficult to understand they are uttered by the same bird! In <a onclick='xc.playFrom(146350, 20);'>00:20</a>, a strange failed call by the same bird.</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>
            <div id='map-canvas'></div>
            </td>
            <td>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

{
    jQuery('#species_nr').val(data.species_nr);
    jQuery('#quick-search-bar > form').submit();
    }

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>

            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

        <td> 11:30</td>
      
        <td>France</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=44.3494&long=-1.067&loc=Parentis-en-Born%2C+Landes+forest%2C+Aquitaine">Parentis-en-Born, Landes forest, Aquitaine</a>
        </td>
        <td>40</td>
        <td>flight call, song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Bird singing while flying. It sings while descending to a tree with outstretched wings, in parachute flight, after an undulating ascending flight.    </p>

<p>The flight song is slightly different from the song given by a perched bird. The end differs and lacks the rapid rattle at the end of the phrase. </p>

<p>Open area between two patches of young pines.  </p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>
<p>   </p></div><a class='fancybox' rel='sono' href='http://www.xeno-canto.org/sounds/uploaded/AZHGSLNALD/ffts/XC313713-large.png' title='XC313713: Tree Pipit (Anthus trivialis) by Nicole Bouglouan'>[sono]</a></div></td>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

</script>

    jQuery('#quick-search-bar > form').submit();
    }

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>
            <div id='map-canvas'></div>
            </td>
            <td>
            <div class='map-sidebar'>
            
            <h3>Map Legend</h3>
        
            <div class="map-legend">
                <h4>Subspecies</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/b-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Anthus-trivialis?query=ssp:%22haringtoni%22'>haringtoni</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>Witherby, 1917</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/a-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Anthus-trivialis?query=ssp:%22trivialis%22'>trivialis</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></span></li></ul><h4>Unclassified</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/unspec-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">No subspecies specified</span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/bg-12.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">In background of another recording</span></li> </ul>
            </div>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

    jQuery('#quick-search-bar > form').submit();
    }

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

        <td>Lithuania</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=54.8425&long=25.5824&loc=Buivyd%C5%BEi%C5%B3+seni%C5%ABnija+%28near++Pakaln%C4%97s%29%2C+Vilnius+District+Municipality%2C+Vilnius+County">BuivydÅ¾iÅ³ seniÅ«nija (near  PakalnÄs), Vilnius District Municipality, Vilnius County</a>
        </td>
        <td>160</td>
        <td>flight call, song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Made a highpass filter since at some point there was a chainsaw sound.
At some point in sustained flight with widely open wings and hovering slightly but almost soaring for a bit.
Small bird, wings seems some how triangular and saw it brown from below.
In a conifer forest, some 25-30 m canopy, relatively clear undergrowth, with mosses and small bushes such as blueberries.
Identified as Anthus trivialis by Piotr Szczypinski.</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>
            <div id='map-canvas'></div>
            </td>
            <td>
            <div class='map-sidebar'>
            
            <h3>Map Legend</h3>
        
            <div class="map-legend">
                <h4>Subspecies</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/b-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Anthus-trivialis?query=ssp:%22haringtoni%22'>haringtoni</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>Witherby, 1917</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/a-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Anthus-trivialis?query=ssp:%22trivialis%22'>trivialis</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></span></li></ul><h4>Unclassified</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/unspec-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">No subspecies specified</span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/bg-12.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">In background of another recording</span></li> </ul>

        <td>2012-10-22</td>
        <td> 07.53am</td>
      
        <td>Sweden</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=58.768&long=17.859&loc=Landsort">Landsort</a>
        </td>
        <td>20</td>
        <td>flight call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Migrating bird, either Tree Pipit or Olive backed Pipit. Very late for the former, whilst the latter is very rarein Sweden, though there is an influx of Olive Backed at the moment into western europe. Opinions welcome. Calls not noticed in the field, only picked up when analyzing recording of morning migration..</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();

            <h1>Tree Pipit &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Anthus trivialis</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Anthus'>Anthus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>trivialis</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Anthus_trivialis.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});
